  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add onion and garlic; sauté until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Toss in lemon zest, dill (if using), thyme leaves (if using), and red pepper flakes. Stir well to combine all the ingredients.",
    "Place the cabbage on top of the vegetable mixture, making sure each slice is evenly coated with the herb-spice oil mixture.",
    "Reduce heat to low and cover the pan for about 10-15 minutes until the cabbage leaves are tender but still crisp.",
    "Garnish with fresh parsley before serving."
